HEADWORD: Hippocrates
<hw>Hip*poc"ra*tes</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A famous Greek
physician and medical writer, born in Cos, about 460 <sc>b.
c.</sc></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Hippocrates' sleeve</b></col>, <cd>a conical strainer,
made by stitching together two adjacent sides of a square piece of
cloth, esp. flannel of linen.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hippocratic</ent>⟦br⟧
